---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Data Deletion Request"
  description="How to request deletion of your personal data from Sales Anchor — via Meta Platform or direct email."
  subtitle="Request deletion of your personal data stored in Sales Anchor."
>
  <h1>Data Deletion Request</h1>
  <p>Last updated: 2026-05-20</p>

  <h2>About This Page</h2>
  <p class="text-lg">Sales Anchor provides two methods for users who wish to request deletion of their personal information and related data. This page describes how to submit a request, what data will be deleted, and the expected timeline for our response.</p>

  <h2>1. Who Can Request Deletion</h2>
  <p>Data deletion requests are available for the following two types of individuals:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Users</strong> — Client company staff who log in and use Sales Anchor directly.</li>
    <li><strong>End Users</strong> — Individuals whose data is indirectly processed via Messenger, Instagram, and other channels through which client companies communicate with their customers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Two Ways to Request Deletion</h2>

  <h3>Method 1: Via Meta Platform</h3>
  <p>By revoking Sales Anchor's app access from your Facebook or Instagram account settings, a data deletion request will be automatically sent to Sales Anchor.</p>
  <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Facebook "Settings &amp; Privacy" → "Settings" → "Apps and Websites"</li>
    <li>Find Sales Anchor and select "Remove"</li>
    <li>A deletion request will be automatically sent to Sales Anchor</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Method 2: Direct Email</h3>
  <p>You can also request deletion by sending an email to our support address.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@salesanchor.jp">support@salesanchor.jp</a><br>
    <strong>Recommended Subject:</strong> "Data Deletion Request"
  </p>
  <p>For identity verification, please include the following information in your email:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your name</li>
    <li>Email address used in Sales Anchor, or your Facebook / Instagram account identifier</li>
    <li>Description of the data you wish to delete</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data That Will Be Deleted</h2>

  <h3>For Users</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Account information (login ID, name, email address, etc.)</li>
    <li>Session information and login history</li>
    <li>Data you have entered in Sales Anchor</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>For End Users</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Meta Platform identifiers (Page-Scoped ID, Instagram-Scoped ID, etc.)</li>
    <li>Message history (Messenger, Instagram Direct Messages)</li>
    <li>Profile information (name, profile picture, etc.)</li>
    <li>Message reactions and read receipts</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Data That Cannot Be Deleted</h3>
  <p>The following data may not be deletable due to legal obligations:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Tax-related documents (retained for 7 years under the Corporate Tax Act)</li>
    <li>Audit logs (retained for 5 years for internal control requirements)</li>
    <li>Litigation-related data (retained until resolution if legally required)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Process and Timeline</h2>
  <p>After receiving your deletion request, we will respond as follows:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Acknowledgment</strong> — We will reply within 24 hours</li>
    <li><strong>Identity verification</strong> — We may request additional information if needed</li>
    <li><strong>Deletion start</strong> — Within 7 business days of your request</li>
    <li><strong>Main database deletion</strong> — Within 14 days of your request</li>
    <li><strong>Complete deletion (including backups)</strong> — Within 30 days of your request</li>
    <li><strong>Completion notification</strong> — A confirmation code (in <code>DEL-YYYYMMDD-xxxx</code> format) will be emailed to you</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>5. Checking Deletion Status</h2>
  <p>After deletion is completed, you can check the status using the confirmation code (<code>DEL-YYYYMMDD-xxxx</code>) at the following URL:</p>
  <p><a href="https://salesanchor.jp/deletion-status">https://salesanchor.jp/deletion-status?code=DEL-YYYYMMDD-xxxx</a></p>

  <h2>6. Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this page or the deletion process, please contact us:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Operated by:</strong> HIGH LIFE JPN (Representative: Shingo Tanizawa)</li>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@salesanchor.jp">support@salesanchor.jp</a></li>
    <li><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday – Friday, 10:00 – 18:00 JST</li>
  </ul>
</LegalLayout>
